          <p>
            This is this third in a series of notebooks designed to show you how to <i>analyze</i> social media data. For demonstration purposes we are looking at tweets sent by CSR-related Twitter accounts &#8212; accounts related to ethics, equality, the environment, etc. &#8212; of Fortune 200 firms in 2013. We assume you have already downloaded the data and have completed the steps taken in <a href="http://nbviewer.ipython.org/github/gdsaxton/PANDAS/blob/master/Chapter%201%20-%20Import%20Data%2C%20Select%20Cases%20and%20Variables%2C%20Save%20DataFrame.ipynb" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Chapter 1</a> and <a href="http://nbviewer.ipython.org/github/gdsaxton/PANDAS/blob/master/Chapter%202%20-%20Aggregating%20and%20Analyzing%20Data%20by%20Twitter%20Account.ipynb" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Chapter 2</a>. In this third notebook I will show you how to conduct various <i>temporal</i> analyses of the Twitter data. Essentially, we will be taking the tweet-level data and aggregating to the account level.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">

      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <h3 id="Convert-created_at-to-time-variable">
            Convert created_at to time variable<a class="anchor-link" href="#Convert-created_at-to-time-variable">&#182;</a>
          </h3>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <p>
            To work with time, we first have to have a variable in our dataframe that indicates time. We will use the <i>created_at</i> column, which represents the time at which the tweet was created. In the following line we will convert this variable from text format to python&#8217;s <i>datetime</i> format.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[16]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">dtypes</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="mi">8</span><span class="p">]</span>
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="output_wrapper">
        <div class="output">
          <div class="output_area">
            <div class="prompt output_prompt">
              Out[16]:
            </div>
            
            <div class="output_text output_subarea output_execute_result">
              <pre>created_at           object
content              object
tweet_id_str         object
language             object
retweeted_status     object
entities_hashtags    object
entities_mentions    object
entities_urls        object
dtype: object</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[17]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;created_at&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;created_at&#39;</span><span class="p">])</span>
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <p>
            Let&#8217;s take another look at the column types. This time we&#8217;ll just look at the first 8 columns, using python&#8217;s splicing capabilities (the &#8216;[:8]&#8217; command tells us we want to return up to the 8th column; this is a useful tool for other applications as well). We see that the <i>created_at</i> column is now a datetime64 object. We now will now be able to manipulate the data &#8212; sorting, indexing, aggregating, and the like &#8212; based on time.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

          <p>

You might think of the index as a tool for organizing or categorizing your data. For instance, will you organize your data alphabetically, by organization, by time, by location, or by whether it includes a photo? Each of these would require a different index variable. What we are going to do here is set the index to be our <i>created_at</i> variable. This will allow us to manipulate the data by time.

          <p>
            Look at the far-left column in bold above. That&#8217;s our index column, and it&#8217;s no longer 0,1,2 but rather our <i>created_at</i> variable. We have effectively told PANDAS that each row (i.e., each tweet) is ready to be indexed according to the values of the <i>created_at</i> column, which, as we did earlier, is a <i>datetime</i> variable.
          </p>

    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">

      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <h2 id="Generate-and-Plot-Number-of-Tweets-over-Different-Time-Periods">
            Generate and Plot Number of Tweets over Different Time Periods<a class="anchor-link" href="#Generate-and-Plot-Number-of-Tweets-over-Different-Time-Periods">&#182;</a>
          </h2>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <p>
            Recall that in <a href="http://nbviewer.ipython.org/github/gdsaxton/PANDAS/blob/master/Chapter%202%20-%20Aggregating%20and%20Analyzing%20Data%20by%20Twitter%20Account.ipynb" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Chapter 2</a> we took our tweet-level dataframe and converted it to an account-level dataframe by aggregating the tweets based on the account variable. We did this by first writing an aggregation function and second by applying that function with a <i>groupby</i> command. We&#8217;re going to do something similar here except that we&#8217;ll be aggregating by time; differently put, we will be &#8220;collapsing&#8221; the data by time rather than by Twitter account.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            As in the last chapter, our first step is to create a function to spell out which variables (columns) from our dataframe that we wish to keep and/or aggregate. Specifically, the following function is first designed to produce a variable called <i>Number_of_tweets</i> that is a <i>count</i> of the number of tweets sent; we are basing this on the &#8220;content&#8221; column but we could have chosen others. This is the same function written in Chapter 2, except that we don&#8217;t need the second and third variables
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <h3 id="Generate-and-Plot-Daily-Counts">
            Generate and Plot Daily Counts<a class="anchor-link" href="#Generate-and-Plot-Daily-Counts">&#182;</a>
          </h3>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <p>
            First, let&#8217;s analyze the data by day of the year. To do this, we need to convert our tweet-level dataset &#8212; a dataset where each row is dedicated to one of the 32,330 tweets &#8212; to a daily dataset. This process is called <i>aggregation</i> and the output will be a new dataframe with 365 rows &#8212; one per day.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            In the following block of code we will now <i>apply</i> the above function to our dataframe. Note the <i>groupby</i> command again &#8212; same as in Chapter 2. This is how we aggregate the data. We are asking PANDAS to create a new dataframe, called <i>daily_count</i>, and asking that this new dataframe be based on aggregating our original dataframe by the <i>index</i> column, applying the function <i>f</i> we wrote above. In other words, we are going to our original dataframe of 32,330 tweets, and aggregating or collapsing that data based on the day of the year it was sent. We are thus converting our tweet-level dataset with 32,330 rows into a daily dataset with 365 rows. As you can see in the output, there are 365 observations in this new dataframe &#8212; one per day.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            Notice also that we are accessing the &#8220;date&#8221; element of our index variable (see <i>index.date</i>). Here you&#8217;ll start to see the power of the Python&#8217;s <i>datetime</i> variables &#8212; by specifying &#8220;.date&#8221;, we are telling PANDAS we want to access only the particular day/month/year combination indicated included in the <i>created_at</i> column.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[75]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">daily_count</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groupby</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">apply</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="k">print</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">daily_count</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">daily_count</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">head</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre>

            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="c1">#mpl.style.use(&#39;fivethirtyeight&#39;)</span>
<span class="n">mpl</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">style</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">use</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;ggplot&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1">#daily_plot = daily_count[&#39;Negativ_pct&#39;][26:].plot(kind=&#39;line&#39;,  lw=2.5, alpha=0.75, legend=True, x_compat=True)</span>
<span class="n">weekly_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">weekly_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Negativ_pct&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;line&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">lw</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.75</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">linestyle</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">":"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">legend</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_compat</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">weekly_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">weekly_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;POLIT_pct&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;line&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>  <span class="n">lw</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">2.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.75</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">legend</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_compat</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">weekly_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">weekly_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Means_pct&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;line&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>  <span class="n">lw</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.75</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">linestyle</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;-.&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">legend</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_compat</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">weekly_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">weekly_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Vice_pct&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;line&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>  <span class="n">lw</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">2.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.75</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">legend</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_compat</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1">#color=seaborn_blue,</span>

<span class="c1"># I CAN JUST USE THIS AS A SHORTHAND</span>

<span class="n">ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Proportion of All Words&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">13</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)</span>

                   <span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="si">% o</span><span class="s1">f Words in *Vice* Dictionary&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span>

            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">mpl</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">style</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">use</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;fivethirtyeight&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">mpl</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">style</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">use</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;ggplot&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>


<span class="n">sns</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_style</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"whitegrid"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">rcParams</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;figure.figsize&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">daily_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">daily_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number_of_tweets&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;line&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>  <span class="n">lw</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">linestyle</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">":"</span><span class="p">,</span>  
                                                  <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.75</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">legend</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_compat</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">daily_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number_of_original_tweets&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;line&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>  <span class="n">lw</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">2.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.75</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">legend</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_compat</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>


<span class="c1">#color=seaborn_blue,</span>
<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">11</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi"></span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"center"</span><span class="p">)</span>  <span class="c1">#SET FONT PROPERTIES OF X-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">yticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">11</span><span class="p">)</span>                              <span class="c1">#SET FONT PROPERTIES OF Y-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>

<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Date&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">13</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)</span>    <span class="c1">#SET X-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO TOP OF LABEL</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;# Tweets (Messages)&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">13</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">#SET Y-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO RIGHT OF LABEL</span>

<span class="c1">#daily_plot.set_xlabel(&#39;&#39;, weight=&#39;bold&#39;, fontsize=13, labelpad=20)    #SET X-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO TOP OF LABEL</span>
<span class="c1">#daily_plot.set_ylabel(&#39;&#39;, weight=&#39;bold&#39;, fontsize=13, labelpad=20) #SET Y-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO RIGHT OF LABEL</span>

<span class="c1">#http://nbviewer.ipython.org/gist/olgabot/5357268  ### LIST OF OPTIONS</span>
<span class="c1">#legend(fontsize=&#39;x-small&#39;,loc=2,labelspacing=0.1, frameon=False)#.draggable()</span>
<span class="c1">#daily_plot.legend_ = None</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">&#39;All Messages (including Retweets)&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;Original Messages&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> 
           <span class="n">loc</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;upper right&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">11</span><span class="p">)</span>


<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tick_params</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;x&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">#SET PADDING ABOVE X-AXIS LABELS</span>

    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[301]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">mpl</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">style</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">use</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;fivethirtyeight&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">mpl</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">style</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">use</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;ggplot&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>


<span class="n">sns</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_style</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"whitegrid"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">rcParams</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;figure.figsize&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">daily_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">daily_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number_of_tweets&#39;</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="mi">11</span><span class="p">:]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;line&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>  <span class="n">lw</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">linestyle</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">":"</span><span class="p">,</span> 
                                                       <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.75</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">legend</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_compat</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">daily_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number_of_original_tweets&#39;</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="mi">11</span><span class="p">:]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;line&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>  <span class="n">lw</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">2.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.75</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">legend</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_compat</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>


<span class="c1">#color=seaborn_blue,</span>
<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">11</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi"></span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"center"</span><span class="p">)</span>  <span class="c1">#SET FONT PROPERTIES OF X-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">yticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">11</span><span class="p">)</span>                              <span class="c1">#SET FONT PROPERTIES OF Y-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>

<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Date&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">13</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)</span>    <span class="c1">#SET X-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO TOP OF LABEL</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;# Tweets (Messages)&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">13</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">#SET Y-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO RIGHT OF LABEL</span>

<span class="c1">#daily_plot.set_xlabel(&#39;&#39;, weight=&#39;bold&#39;, fontsize=13, labelpad=20)    #SET X-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO TOP OF LABEL</span>
<span class="c1">#daily_plot.set_ylabel(&#39;&#39;, weight=&#39;bold&#39;, fontsize=13, labelpad=20) #SET Y-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO RIGHT OF LABEL</span>

<span class="c1">#http://matplotlib.org/users/legend_guide.html</span>
<span class="c1">#http://nbviewer.ipython.org/gist/olgabot/5357268  ### LIST OF OPTIONS</span>
<span class="c1">#legend(fontsize=&#39;x-small&#39;,loc=2,labelspacing=0.1, frameon=False)#.draggable()</span>
<span class="c1">#daily_plot.legend_ = None</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">&#39;All Messages (including Retweets)&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;Original Messages&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> 
           <span class="n">loc</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;upper right&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">11</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tick_params</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;x&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">#SET PADDING ABOVE X-AXIS LABELS</span>
<span class="c1">#Set x axis label on top of plot, set label text --&gt; https://datasciencelab.wordpress.com/2013/12/21/beautiful-plots-with-pandas-and-matplotlib/</span>
<span class="c1">#daily_plot.xaxis.set_label_position(&#39;top&#39;)</span>

<span class="c1">#savefig(&#39;daily counts.png&#39;, bbox_inches=&#39;tight&#39;, dpi=300, format=&#39;png&#39;)   #SAVE PLOT IN PNG FORMAT</span>
<span class="c1">#savefig(&#39;daily counts.svg&#39;, bbox_inches=&#39;tight&#39;, dpi=600, format=&#39;svg&#39;)   #SAVE PLOT IN PNG FORMAT</span>
<span class="n">savefig</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;daily counts (close-up starting 4-17).png&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">bbox_inches</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;tight&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">edgecolor</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;white&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">facecolor</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;white&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">dpi</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">600</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">format</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;png&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="c1">#savefig(&#39;daily counts (close-up starting 4-17).svg&#39;, bbox_inches=&#39;tight&#39;, edgecolor = &#39;white&#39;, facecolor=&#39;white&#39;, dpi=600, format=&#39;svg&#39;)</span>
<span class="c1">#savefig(&#39;daily counts (no axis labels).png&#39;, bbox_inches=&#39;tight&#39;, edgecolor = &#39;white&#39;, facecolor=&#39;white&#39;, dpi=600, format=&#39;png&#39;)</span>

      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <h4 id="Output-account-level-data-to-CSV-file">
            Output account-level data to CSV file<a class="anchor-link" href="#Output-account-level-data-to-CSV-file">&#182;</a>
          </h4>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <p>
            As shown in Chapter 1, it is simple to save the output of any of the temporally aggregated files we have created above. For example, let&#8217;s output <i>daily_count</i> to a CSV file. This will give us a file with 365 rows and two columns above: <i>date</i> and <i>Number_of_tweets</i>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[342]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">daily_count</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number of Tweets per Day.csv&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <p>
            PANDAS can output to <a href="http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/io.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">a number of different formats</a>. I most commonly use <i>to_csv, to_excel, to_json</i>, and <i>to_pickle</i>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[343]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">

    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <h3 id="Generate-and-Plot-Day-of-the-Week-Tweets">
            Generate and Plot Day-of-the-Week Tweets<a class="anchor-link" href="#Generate-and-Plot-Day-of-the-Week-Tweets">&#182;</a>
          </h3>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <p>
            Now let&#8217;s create a dataframe with a count of the number of tweets per day of the week. We can apply the same function <i>f</i> and use the same index variable <i>date</i>. The only difference is that we will access the &#8220;weekday&#8221; element of our index variable <i>created_at</i>. It bears repeating that we converted <i>created_at</i> to a python <i>datetime</i> variable and, fortunately for us, this type of variable has a number of different attributes we can access, including <i>second, minute, hour, day, weekday, month</i>, and <i>year</i>.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            In the following block of code we will now apply our aggregating function <i>f</i> to our dataframe <i>df</i> and use the <i>groupby</i> command again &#8212; only this time we are aggregating on the <i>weekday</i> attribute of our datetime variable. We are thus asking PANDAS to create a new dataframe, called <i>weekday_count</i>, and asking that this new dataframe be based on aggregating our original dataframe by <i>index.weekday</i>, applying the function <i>f</i> we wrote above. In other words, we are going to our original dataframe of 32,330 tweets, and aggregating or collapsing that data based on the day of the week it was sent. We are thus converting our tweet-level dataset with 32,330 rows into a daily dataset with 7 rows.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[315]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">weekday_count</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groupby</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">weekday</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">apply</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="k">print</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">weekday_count</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">weekday_count</span>
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

              <pre><span></span><span class="n">day_of_week_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">weekday_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number_of_tweets&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bar&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.9</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">arange</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">7</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">weekday_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;day&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi"></span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">#, ha ="left") </span>

<span class="c1">#days = [&#39;Monday&#39;, &#39;Tuesday&#39;, &#39;Wednesday&#39;, &#39;Thursday&#39;, &#39;Friday&#39;, &#39;Saturday&#39;, &#39;Sunday&#39;]</span>
<span class="c1">#xticks(np.arange(7), days, rotation = 0,fontsize = 9) #, ha ="left") </span>

    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <p>
            We see that, not surprisingly, there are many fewer tweets sent on the weekend over the course of 2013.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <h3 id="Hour-of-Day-Counts">
            Hour-of-Day Counts<a class="anchor-link" href="#Hour-of-Day-Counts">&#182;</a>
          </h3>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <p>
            We might also be interested in the hour of the day that the tweets are sent. We only need to access our index&#8217;s <i>hour</i> attribute to accomplish this.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[198]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">hourly_count</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groupby</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">hour</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">apply</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="k">print</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">hourly_count</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">hourly_count</span>
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <p>
            However, it is showing the hours in the &#8220;pythonic&#8221; way &#8212; from 0 to 23. We can fix that by adding a list with the hours 1-24 and then invoking that list in our xticks command. The plot below also adds labels for the x and y axes and saves the output in PNG format.`
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[223]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">hourly_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">hourly_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number_of_tweets&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;line&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">hours</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">25</span><span class="p">))</span>                                                <span class="c1">#GENERATE LIST FROM 1 TO 24</span>
<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">arange</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">24</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">hours</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi"></span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">)</span>                  <span class="c1">#USE THE CUSTOM TICKS</span>

<span class="n">hourly_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Hour of the Day&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">)</span>     <span class="c1">#SET X-AXIS LABEL, ADD PADDING TO TOP OF X-AXIS LABEL</span>
<span class="n">hourly_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;# Tweets (Messages)&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">#SET Y-AXIS LABEL, ADD PADDING TO RIGHT OF Y-AXIS LABEL</span>

<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi"></span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"center"</span><span class="p">)</span>                          <span class="c1">#SET FONT SIZE FOR X-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">yticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">)</span>                                                      <span class="c1">#SET FONT SIZE FOR Y-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tick_params</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;x&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>                                   <span class="c1">#SET PADDING ABOVE X-AXIS LABELS</span>

<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend_</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">None</span>                                                 <span class="c1">#TURN OFF LEGEND</span>

<span class="n">savefig</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;hourly counts - line graph.png&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">bbox_inches</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;tight&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">edgecolor</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;white&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">facecolor</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;white&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> 
        <span class="n">dpi</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">600</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">format</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;png&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">

        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">hourly_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">hourly_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number_of_tweets&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bar&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">hours</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">25</span><span class="p">))</span>                                                 <span class="c1">#GENERATE LIST FROM 1 TO 24</span>
<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">arange</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">24</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">hours</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi"></span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">)</span>                   <span class="c1">#USE THE CUSTOM TICKS</span>

<span class="n">hourly_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Hour of the Day&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">)</span>     <span class="c1">#SET X-AXIS LABEL, ADD PADDING TO TOP OF X-AXIS LABEL</span>
<span class="n">hourly_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;# Tweets (Messages)&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">#SET Y-AXIS LABEL, ADD PADDING TO RIGHT OF Y-AXIS LABEL</span>

<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi"></span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"center"</span><span class="p">)</span>                          <span class="c1">#SET FONT SIZE FOR X-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">yticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">)</span>                                                      <span class="c1">#SET FONT SIZE FOR Y-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tick_params</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;x&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>                                   <span class="c1">#SET PADDING ABOVE X-AXIS LABELS</span>

<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend_</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">None</span>                                                 <span class="c1">#TURN OFF LEGEND</span>

<span class="n">savefig</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;hourly counts - bar graph.png&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">bbox_inches</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;tight&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">dpi</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">600</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">edgecolor</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;white&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">facecolor</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;white&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>
        <span class="n">format</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;png&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre>

              <pre><span></span><span class="n">monthly_count</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_pickle</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number of Tweets per Month.pkl&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre>
            </div>

      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <p>
            Using basically the same code as above, we can plot a bar graph of these data. The one change is the second line of code &#8212; here we use the <i>calendar</i> package to help generate a list of the months of the year. Python has a ton of such specialized packages to help same save.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[226]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">monthly_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">monthly_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number_of_tweets&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bar&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">months</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">calendar</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">month_name</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:])</span>                                    <span class="c1">#GENERATE LIST OF MONTHS</span>
<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">arange</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">months</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">8</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi"></span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">)</span>                  <span class="c1">#USE THE CUSTOM TICKS</span>

<span class="n">monthly_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Month of the Year&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">)</span>  <span class="c1">#SET X-AXIS LABEL, ADD PADDING TO TOP OF X-AXIS LABEL</span>
<span class="n">monthly_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;# Tweets (Messages)&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">#SET Y-AXIS LABEL, ADD PADDING TO RIGHT OF Y-AXIS LABEL</span>

<span class="c1">#monthly_plot.set_xlabel(&#39;&#39;, weight=&#39;bold&#39;, labelpad=15)  #SET X-AXIS LABEL, ADD PADDING TO TOP OF X-AXIS LABEL</span>
<span class="c1">#monthly_plot.set_ylabel(&#39;&#39;, weight=&#39;bold&#39;, labelpad=15) #SET Y-AXIS LABEL, ADD PADDING TO RIGHT OF Y-AXIS LABEL</span>

<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi"></span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"center"</span><span class="p">)</span>                          <span class="c1">#SET FONT SIZE FOR X-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">yticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">)</span>                                                      <span class="c1">#SET FONT SIZE FOR Y-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tick_params</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;x&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>                                   <span class="c1">#SET PADDING ABOVE X-AXIS LABELS</span>

<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend_</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">None</span>                                                 <span class="c1">#TURN OFF LEGEND</span>

<span class="n">savefig</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;monthly counts - bar graph.png&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">bbox_inches</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;tight&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">edgecolor</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;white&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">facecolor</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;white&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>
        <span class="n">dpi</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">600</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">format</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;png&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="c1">#savefig(&#39;monthly counts - bar graph (no axis labels).png&#39;, bbox_inches=&#39;tight&#39;, edgecolor = &#39;white&#39;, facecolor=&#39;white&#39;,</span>
<span class="c1">#        dpi=600, format=&#39;png&#39;)</span>
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

        <div class="output">
          <div class="output_area">

      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <h5 id="With-original-and-all-tweets">
            With original and all tweets<a class="anchor-link" href="#With-original-and-all-tweets">&#182;</a>
          </h5>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[338]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">monthly_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">monthly_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number_of_tweets&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bar&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>  <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.85</span><span class="p">,)</span>
<span class="n">monthly_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number_of_original_tweets&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bar&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">seaborn_blue</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alpha</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.90</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">hatch</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"/"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">months</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">calendar</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">month_name</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:])</span>                                    <span class="c1">#GENERATE LIST OF MONTHS</span>
<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">arange</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">months</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">8</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi"></span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">)</span>                  <span class="c1">#USE THE CUSTOM TICKS</span>

<span class="n">monthly_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Month of the Year&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">13</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)</span>  <span class="c1">#SET X-AXIS LABEL, ADD PADDING TO TOP OF X-AXIS LABEL</span>
<span class="n">monthly_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;# Tweets (Messages)&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">13</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">#SET Y-AXIS LABEL, ADD PADDING TO RIGHT OF Y-AXIS LABEL</span>

<span class="c1">#monthly_plot.set_xlabel(&#39;&#39;, weight=&#39;bold&#39;, labelpad=15)  #SET X-AXIS LABEL, ADD PADDING TO TOP OF X-AXIS LABEL</span>
<span class="c1">#monthly_plot.set_ylabel(&#39;&#39;, weight=&#39;bold&#39;, labelpad=15) #SET Y-AXIS LABEL, ADD PADDING TO RIGHT OF Y-AXIS LABEL</span>

<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">11</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi"></span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"center"</span><span class="p">)</span>                          <span class="c1">#SET FONT SIZE FOR X-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">yticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">11</span><span class="p">)</span>                                                      <span class="c1">#SET FONT SIZE FOR Y-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tick_params</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;x&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>                                   <span class="c1">#SET PADDING ABOVE X-AXIS LABELS</span>

<span class="c1">#daily_plot.legend_ = None                                                 #TURN OFF LEGEND</span>
<span class="n">monthly_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">&#39;All Messages (including Retweets)&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;Original Messages&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> 
           <span class="n">loc</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;upper right&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">11</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">savefig</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;monthly counts - bar graph (with retweets).png&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">bbox_inches</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;tight&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">edgecolor</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;white&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">facecolor</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;white&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span>
        <span class="n">dpi</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">600</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">format</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;png&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="c1">#savefig(&#39;monthly counts - bar graph (no axis labels).png&#39;, bbox_inches=&#39;tight&#39;, edgecolor = &#39;white&#39;, facecolor=&#39;white&#39;,</span>
<span class="c1">#        dpi=600, format=&#39;png&#39;)</span>
</pre>

            In case you ever wanted to, you can also access the minute at which the tweets were posted. Note that the <i>minute</i> attribute refers to the minute of the hour, not the minute of the day. That is, the <i>n</i> is 60.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[212]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">minute_count</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groupby</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">minute</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">apply</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="k">print</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">minute_count</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">minute_count</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">head</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

          <h3 id="Super-Ridiculous:-Number-of-Tweets-per-Second">
            Super Ridiculous: Number of Tweets per Second<a class="anchor-link" href="#Super-Ridiculous:-Number-of-Tweets-per-Second">&#182;</a>
          </h3>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <p>
            Note that the <i>second</i> attribute refers to the second of the minute, so the <i>n</i> is 60.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">

        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">second_count</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groupby</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">second</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">apply</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">second_count</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">head</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre>

        </div>

    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <h2 id="Alternative-Plotting-Styles">
            Alternative Plotting Styles<a class="anchor-link" href="#Alternative-Plotting-Styles">&#182;</a>
          </h2>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
      <div class="prompt input_prompt">
      </div>
      
      <div class="inner_cell">
        <div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
          <p>
            I like the <i>Seaborn</i> styles shown above. However, you might want to play around with some of the other styles available to you. First, let&#8217;s try the plot with the &#8216;default&#8217; mpl_style. For each style, I&#8217;ll show you a line plot (# of tweets per day of the year) and a bar graph (# of tweets per day of the week).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[228]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_option</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;display.mpl_style&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;default&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1"># Make the graphs a bit prettier</span>
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[229]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">rcParams</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;figure.figsize&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">
          In&nbsp;[230]:
        </div>
        
        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">daily_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">daily_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number_of_tweets&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;line&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">lw</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.75</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">legend</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_compat</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Month&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">)</span>    <span class="c1">#SET X-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO TOP OF LABEL</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;# Tweets (Messages)&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">#SET Y-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO RIGHT OF LABEL</span>

<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">30</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"left"</span><span class="p">)</span>  <span class="c1">#SET FONT PROPERTIES OF X-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">yticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">)</span>                              <span class="c1">#SET FONT PROPERTIES OF Y-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend_</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">None</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tick_params</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">axis</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;x&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="input">

        <div class="inner_cell">

              <pre><span></span><span class="n">mpl</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">style</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">use</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;dark_background&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">daily_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">daily_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number_of_tweets&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;line&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">lw</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.75</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">legend</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_compat</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Month&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">)</span>    <span class="c1">#SET X-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO TOP OF LABEL</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;# Tweets (Messages)&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">#SET Y-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO RIGHT OF LABEL</span>
<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">30</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"left"</span><span class="p">)</span>  <span class="c1">#SET FONT PROPERTIES OF X-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">yticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">)</span>                              <span class="c1">#SET FONT PROPERTIES OF Y-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend_</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">None</span>

</pre>

              <pre><span></span><span class="n">daily_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">daily_count</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Number_of_tweets&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;line&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">lw</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">alpha</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.75</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">legend</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x_compat</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Month&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">)</span>    <span class="c1">#SET X-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO TOP OF LABEL</span>
<span class="n">daily_plot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;# Tweets (Messages)&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">weight</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;bold&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">labelpad</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">#SET Y-AXIS LABEL; ADD PADDING TO RIGHT OF LABEL</span>
<span class="n">xticks</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fontsize</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">rotation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">30</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"left"</span><span class="p">)</span>  <span class="c1">#SET FONT PROPERTIES OF X-AXIS TICK LABELS</span>

    <div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
      <div class="input">
        <div class="prompt input_prompt">

        <div class="inner_cell">
          <div class="input_area">
            <div class=" highlight hl-ipython2">
              <pre><span></span><span class="n">mpl</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">style</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">use</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;ggplot&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre>

          </div>
        </div>
